      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CYNICAL (1) is a progressive gelding who stretched his winning streak to six when he led from a couple of spots wider and kept going to score by 6.5m at this circuit and distance last time. Takes a step up in in grade but has plenty of upside and possesses the early speed to take advantage of the inside draw. SINALOA (7) was last seen when midfield in the Riverina Championships final in April and put together a string of placings prior, highlighted by a third in the Chariots of Fire. Readied with two trials and flies fresh with three wins and a placing from four attempts. SAO PAULO SIMBA (5) had to work when resuming as favourite and only beat one home but he has a fine record at this shorter distance, recording four wins and two placings from seven attempts so look for improvement. DEMON BLUE NZ (2) is back in winning form. Drawn well so can be in the finish again.",
